My 2cp...<br>
   Who cares if he cant be snared, as long as the mob aggroes on you, any attempt thereafter should be considered a KS.<br>
   I too do not like the situation.  Too many people are fighting over things, it would be nice if there was a solution, but i dont see one in the near future.  People need to recognize that something is camped.. (If there is a &quot;camp&quot; left).  They should respect that person, and try again later, simple as that.  Some people in the lower level guilds trying to kill mobs are just thrown aside simply because they may not have the man power readily avaliable to kill him.  People should respect that.<br>
   Some people set up a guild raid for mobs such as these...They Blast their ass sitting and waiting for the spawn in hopes of holding it down till the raid is scheduled to begin.  At this time, People begin loggin on to help the guy,  but low and behold, some uber guild comes in and steals it.  AKA. Massive waste of time for the cleric, his guild, and just makes tempers flare...<br>
   Things out to go back to the way they were, people should just wait their turn.  This way it would be much fairer to the person camping it who is in a smaller guild (or no guild for that fact), it would save the time of the guild in question, and could stop a lot of this mindless crap fest about who stole what from who.<br>
<br>
Wewen Frostpaw<br>
